      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on primary hemolysis QoI; Richardson extrapolation applied to at least three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study completed. GCI on volume-averaged scalar shear stress: 2.1% (fine-medium), 3.8% (medium-coarse). Richardson extrapolation applied formally. Discretization uncertainty propagated to NIH prediction: ±3.2%. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented and matched to CFD boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions were documented in the bench protocol; however, inlet velocity profiles were measured only at a single nominal flow rate (4.5 L/min) and extrapolated to the remaining four operating points using a scaling assumption. Temperature and hematocrit variability across test runs (±1.8°C, ±2.1% Hct) were not propagated into the CFD boundary conditions. The mismatch between the assumed fully-developed inlet profile and the actual upstream connector geometry introduces unquantified boundary condition uncertainty at off-nominal operating points. Achieved level 1 falls below the required level 2 for this COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) computed for primary QoI at all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error between predicted and measured NIH computed at all five operating points: range 4.1%–12.6%, mean 8.3%. Validation uncertainty (combining experimental measurement uncertainty and numerical uncertainty) estimated at ±11.4% at 95% confidence. All predictions fall within combined validation uncertainty bands. Metric satisfies level 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH and RH index) directly maps to the clinical endpoint of concern; scalar stress exposure used as surrogate is justified by published hemolysis models.",
      "rationale": "NIH and relative hemolysis index RH are the regulatory QoIs for CPB device submissions. Scalar stress exposure (Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model) is the accepted CFD surrogate for erythrocyte damage in rotary blood pumps. QoI relevance is well-established in the literature and accepted by FDA guidance. Level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same device geometry and fluid (porcine blood or blood analog) at operating conditions spanning the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — identical to the COU device. Porcine blood used per ASTM F1841. Five operating points span the clinical flow-speed envelope (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Geometric and physiological similarity sufficient for MRL 2. Level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to at least 1×10⁻⁴ for all transport equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All steady-state simulations converged to continuity residual 1×10⁻⁵ and momentum residuals 1×10⁻⁵ or better. Mass imbalance < 0.005% for all five operating points. Solver error contribution to QoI uncertainty negligible relative to discretization and model-form uncertainties."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup by a second qualified analyst; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second CFD analyst using an internal 22-item checklist covering geometry import, boundary condition assignment, turbulence model selection, and post-processing scripts. One minor discrepancy (incorrect reference pressure location) identified and corrected prior to final runs. Use error risk assessed as low."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison to experimental velocity data; hemolysis damage model selection justified by published validation studies.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω selected over realizable k-ε based on PIV comparison (RMS velocity error 6.2% vs. 9.8%). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model selected based on published validation corpus for rotary blood pumps. Model-form uncertainty estimated at ±4.7% contribution to NIH. Sensitivity analysis documented. Level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
